  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: e9620f8c34305754d8cc9a7e49e852d9, type: 3}
  m_Name: Tutorial_en
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_LocaleId:
    m_Code: en
  m_SharedData: {fileID: 11400000, guid: e00198e87a257ff41b02cc989c3a409a, type: 2}
  m_Metadata:
    m_Items:
    - rid: 2319839819189715041
  m_TableData:
  - m_Id: 11264212992
    m_Localized: Hello! Welcome to Pantory!
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items:
      - rid: 2319839819189715041
  - m_Id: 438890283008
    m_Localized: Pantory is a factory management simulation game.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 575934971904
    m_Localized: First, a quick overview of the UI. You can reopen this help anytime
      with the (?) button on each main panel.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1678642659328
    m_Localized: Credits and Research Points are shown at the top left; tap there
      for details.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2291514359808
    m_Localized: This container displays the employment status, allocation status,
      and satisfaction level of employees.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2320476028928
    m_Localized: This strip shows the in-game date and clock, plus buttons to reopen
      the tutorial or open settings.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2777508364288
    m_Localized: Use these icons to jump between Storage, Orders, Market, Staff, Research,
      News, and Finance. You can also press F1 through F9 for the same shortcuts.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 5943566155776
    m_Localized: Logistics is the core of your factory. Build a line by connecting
      stations and production buildings with roads, then keep every input and output
      direction aligned so packets can continue moving without delay.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 7203816095744
    m_Localized: Typical flow is Unload → roads → production buildings → roads →
      Load. Unload pulls raw materials in, factories process them, and Load sends
      finished goods toward storage.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 7579063697408
    m_Localized: Building buttons are grouped by category. Distribution includes
      roads, splitter, and tunnel. Many production buildings unlock through research.
      Use the Blueprint tab to save layouts and place them again later.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 7894026567680
    m_Localized: Place buildings and roads from this panel. Select an item, preview
      rotation on the grid, and click to build. Hold placement input to lay long
      road lines quickly.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 8131256401920
    m_Localized: Track resource inventory in this panel. If a line stalls, first
      check whether upstream materials are available, then verify road direction,
      building orientation, and whether outputs are connected to valid destinations.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 9056704413696
    m_Localized: Good logistics design means short paths, clear direction, and balanced
      outputs. Expand gradually, watch for bottlenecks, and use splitter/tunnel strategically
      to keep throughput stable as your factory grows.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 11779361357824
    m_Localized: This panel toggles remove mode, rotates the selected building, and
      can auto-assign workers when you place production buildings. Removing a building
      clears its worker assignments—recheck staffing after big layout changes.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 12960301203456
    m_Localized: This is the storage panel. This panel shows you the inventory of
      resources you currently have.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 13340426780672
    m_Localized: Every resource belongs to a category; use the filters here to narrow
      the list.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 17836750028800
    m_Localized: This is the Orders panel. Clients request materials; accept a contract,
      then deliver the listed resources before the deadline.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 17928651423744
    m_Localized: Filter by client type—Market, Company, then Government. Orders usually
      grow larger in that order, and your company Wealth can scale them further.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18539786682368
    m_Localized: Toggle this switch to show only accepted orders you are currently
      fulfilling.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 18834268766208
    m_Localized: Pick a client in this list to see their available contracts on the
      right.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 19061579071488
    m_Localized: New contracts appear here. Click one to accept it, then deliver the
      listed resources before time runs out.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 19716532224000
    m_Localized: This is the Market panel. Here you can buy and sell resources and
      view information about competing companies.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 22018345287680
    m_Localized: Here you can choose whether to display the resource view or the
      trader (competitor) view via the button.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 22020337582080
    m_Localized: This is the Resource View. You can adjust your current resource
      purchase and sale volume here.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 24215317528576
    m_Localized: Resource information is displayed here.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 24483870425088
    m_Localized: The price history of resources is visually displayed here.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 24698149027840
    m_Localized: This is the Trader (Competitor) View. You can view information about
      each trader.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 36510642880512
    m_Localized: This is the panel where you can manage your employees.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 36904429305856
    m_Localized: This shows your current management capacity. A certain number of
      managers are required per employee. If you are short on managers, employee
      satisfaction will be penalized.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 37440536854528
    m_Localized: Employee satisfaction is affected by many factors. You can see what
      is affecting it here.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 37828904239104
    m_Localized: Employee efficiency depends on satisfaction, and that efficiency
      directly affects building work speed and production throughput.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 38302378246144
    m_Localized: The easiest way to raise employee satisfaction is to pay them more.
      Lower pay will reduce it.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 39086448852992
    m_Localized: Four roles—Workers and Technicians staff buildings on the grid,
      Researchers generate Research Points (RP), and Managers keep the workforce
      covered so satisfaction does not drop.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 39688935456768
    m_Localized: Here, you can decide whether to hire or fire employees. Hiring or
      firing employees costs credits, and firing employees will decrease their satisfaction.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2561770013474816
    m_Localized: This is the research panel. You can unlock buildings and boost productivity.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2562082698838016
    m_Localized: This is where you can see your Research Points (RP) and how many
      Research Points you gain each day.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2562316594200576
    m_Localized: This is a panel where you can see the number of researchers and
      the effects they are receiving.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2562738453102592
    m_Localized: This is the research tree. Finished nodes are tinted, and the next
      linked projects unlock once their prerequisites are met.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2563160425250816
    m_Localized: This is the Finance panel, where you can view your company's growth
      over time.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2564533472608256
    m_Localized: Shows your current monthly growth rate.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2565297930649600
    m_Localized: Shows your current monthly profit.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2566859943985152
    m_Localized: Shows your current company value in a graph.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2566981499109376
    m_Localized: Shows your current credits in a graph.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2578000000000000
    m_Localized: This panel tracks the Labor Union chapter. While it runs, overall workforce
      satisfaction drives how much Union Cohesion rises or falls each day, and the
      union may issue demands you can fulfill for extra cohesion.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2578000000000001
    m_Localized: The event icon and number show how many days remain in this chapter.
      When the counter reaches zero, the union phase ends.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2578000000000002
    m_Localized: These bars preview tomorrow's daily cohesion change from weighted workforce
      satisfaction. The left bar fills left to right for gains above the baseline;
      the right bar fills right to left for losses below it. The label shows the
      exact percent per day.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2578000000000003
    m_Localized: Union Cohesion is the main score for this event, from 0% to 100%. It
      shifts automatically each day from the satisfaction preview above. Reaching
      100% completes the chapter.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2578000000000004
    m_Localized: Each employee role's satisfaction is shown here. Pay levels on the
      Staff panel, avoiding mass layoffs, and completing union requests are the main
      ways to move the daily bars and this cohesion meter.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2578000000000005
    m_Localized: Active union requests are listed here. Each has one requirement—credits,
      resources, or a policy—and a deadline in days. When the requirement is met,
      the row highlights; tap it to complete the request and claim the cohesion reward.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2578100000000000
    m_Localized: This is the Policy panel. Toggle workplace rules that apply ongoing
      effects to production, costs, and employee satisfaction.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2578100000000001
    m_Localized: Each policy can be switched on or off. Some cost credits or RP to
      activate and may run for a limited number of months—read the details before committing.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2578100000000002
    m_Localized: Active policies and their effects are summarized here. Use this list
      to see which bonuses and penalties are currently shaping your factory.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2578200000000000
    m_Localized: This is the News panel. Headlines appear as events unfold—market shifts,
      main-event chapters, and other story beats that can change how you should play.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2578200000000001
    m_Localized: Scroll through active stories here. New articles are added when triggers
      fire; older items drop off as they expire.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 2578200000000002
    m_Localized: Open a headline to read the full article. Many stories hint at price
      moves, union pressure, or research opportunities—check back after big changes.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  references:
    version: 2
